---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

	* Object Store

	* We can store files, videos, audios

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

5 Types

	1. Blobs - Object store as above
	2. Files - File share for cloud
	3. Queues - Queues Ex: Kafka
	4. Tables - NoSQL data store 
	5. Disks - Storage for VMs - managed by VM

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Blob (Binary Large Object)

	* To store Files, videos, documents, large files

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Architecture

	* Storage Account -> Container -> Blob

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

6 Redundancy

	1. LRS (Locally Redundant Storage)
		Data is copied 3 times in same zone

	2. ZRS (Zone Redundant Storage)
		Copied in 3 zones in same region

	3. GRS (Geo Redundant Storage)
		Copied in 3 same zones and copied asynchronously to paired region, accessed on failover 

	4. GZRS (Geo Zone Redundant Storage)
		Copied synchronously to 3 zones and asynchronously to paired region, accessed over failover

	5. RA-GRS (Read Access Geo Zone Redundant Storage)
		Copied synchronously to 3 zones and asynchronously to paired region but read access in secondary region

	6. RA-GZRS (Read Access Geo Zone Redundant Storage)
		Copied in 3 same zones and copied asynchronously to paired region but read access in secondary region

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

3 Types of Storage Tiers

Blobs are uploaded in one of these 3 tiers

	1. Hot 

		* Data accessed frequently
		* High cost
		* Ex: Files, videos...etc

	2. Cool

		* Data accessed infrequently
		* Low cost
		* Must be stored at least 30 days, early deletion fees applies
		* Ex: Short term back...etc

	3. Archive

		* Data for archival
		* Can take hours to retrieve 
		* Must be stored at least 180 days, early deletion fees applies

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Pricing based on following

	1. Redundancy option
	2. Tiers
	3. Capacity

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

We can use connection string to do anything on Storage Account

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

CDN (Content Delivery Network)

Data will get downloaded to nearest Region and will be accessible for user

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Storage Explorer

	* Is an EXE file to see all Storage Accounts and all data
	* Also we can do here as well all access

